Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["GARCH with t innovations", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.406269143060752*^9, 3.406269147568752*^9}, {
   3.530599059624044*^9, 3.530599065584362*^9}, {3.530691073690981*^9, 
   3.530691075674041*^9}, {3.53069147302001*^9, 3.530691474871354*^9}, {
   3.530693029400872*^9, 3.5306930616095943`*^9}, {3.530693180996456*^9, 
   3.530693195629059*^9}, 
   3.530855258670388*^9},ExpressionUUID->"52c3893d-50d3-43e1-b255-\
197318b9894a"],

Cell["\<\

Are the GARCH residuals normally distributed ? Usually the financial assets \
prices are fat-tailed, i.e. the distribution has more weight in the tails \
then a normal distribution. In general, there is a higher probability of \
large gain (or loss) then indicated by the normal distribution. 

Instead of the Gaussian innovations we can use t-distributed innovations.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.4062691559797516`*^9, 3.406269427871752*^9}, 
   3.5296755517986937`*^9, 3.530691101115761*^9, {3.530691203421274*^9, 
   3.530691263909665*^9}, {3.530691298812022*^9, 3.530691587991209*^9}, {
   3.5306916569332542`*^9, 3.530691791578145*^9}, {3.530691826696795*^9, 
   3.5306918520562468`*^9}, {3.530691904724057*^9, 3.5306919544418077`*^9}, {
   3.5306920106236897`*^9, 3.530692199564807*^9}, {3.530693206853312*^9, 
